data.title: Missy Elliott adds Midwest dates to 2024 tour, how to get tickets
data.meta_description: The “Out Of This World” tour dates have been expanded to include a show in Cleveland, Ohio and another night in Rosemont, IL just outside of Chicago. Purchase tickets from $69.
data.text:
The “Out Of This World” tour dates have been expanded to include a show in Cleveland, Ohio and another night in Rosemont, IL just outside of Chicago. Purchase tickets from $69.

Find available tickets on SeatGeek, Vivid Seats, and StubHub.

The Missy Elliott “Out Of This World” tour with Busta Rhymes, Ciara, and Timbaland now offers performances in Orlando, Florida on July 30; Cleveland, Ohio on August 14; Toronto, Ontario on August 20; and a second night in Rosemont, Illinois on August 23, northwest of Chicago.

Iconic pop star, rapper, producer, and songwriter Missy Elliott has influenced music across genres since the release of her debut album, “Supa Dupa Fly,” back in 1997, working with Janet Jackson, Mariah Carey, Beyoncé, Katy Perry, Lil’ Kim, Whitney Houston, and more throughout her decades-long career. She’s received multiple MTV Video Music Awards, Grammys, an honorary doctorate from Berklee College of Music, and a recent induction into the Rock & Roll Hall of Fame, among other accolades. Per her website, “Missy Elliott has inspired people for a multitude of reasons, across a plethora of fields, and it’s safe to say that her work is nowhere near done. Just when you think she can’t top herself, she does it, with masterful flair and a grin.”

“Out of This World: The Missy Elliott Experience Tour,” also featuring longtime hip-hop stars Busta Rhymes, Ciara, and Timbaland — one of her closest collaborators — is Missy Elliott’s first headlining tour, hitting venues like the Crypto.com Arena in Los Angeles, Newark’s Prudential Center, and Little Caesars Arena in Detroit. See below for upcoming Midwest tour dates.
